title: Autobiography of the Rev. Dr. Alexander Carlyle, Minister of Inveresk,
author: Carlyle, Alexander
snippet: The estate was sold, and he now lived in a house in Inveresk, opposite to Mr Colt's, called Rosebank, built near a hundred years before by Sir Thomas Young, Knight.
